{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-lesson-template-js","path":"/opening-vim","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"before-you-do\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#before-you-do\" aria-label=\"before you do permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Before you do</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Navigate to an empty directory (create your own).  We will be doing a bit of\nediting.</li>\n<li>\n<p>Ensure you have no vim rc active.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If you are using vim, rename ~/.vimrc -> ~/.vimrc2</li>\n<li>If you are using nvim, rename ~/.config/nvim/init.vim -> ~/.config/nvim/init.vim2</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"exercises\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#exercises\" aria-label=\"exercises permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Exercises</h3>\n<p>We will be using curl to grab a few exercises throughout this class.  Here is\nan example.</p>\n<h4 id=\"note\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#note\" aria-label=\"note permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Note</h4>\n<p>Notice that i name the downloaded file then <code class=\"language-text\">&amp;&amp; vim name</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">curl</span> https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ThePrimeagen/vim-fundamentals/master/course-website/lessons/exercise-0-hjkl-x.md <span class=\"token operator\">></span> exercise.md <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token function\">vim</span> exercise.md</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"one-more-thing-before-we-start\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#one-more-thing-before-we-start\" aria-label=\"one more thing before we start permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>One more thing before we start</h2>\n<p>We are going to start from when Adam met Eve.  So if you have some experience\nyou can probably skip the next couple sections.  There is always valuable\ninformation that may not know, but it may not be worth the time.</p>\n<p>When I started, vim motions were chief most important, not vim itself.  This\ncourse will reverse that.  Vim will be the spot light, motions will actually\ntake a backseat.  I will show you what is available though.</p>\n<h2 id=\"lets-open-vim\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lets-open-vim\" aria-label=\"lets open vim permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lets open vim!</h2>\n<p>So you are in an empty directory, lets do this! Simply type <code class=\"language-text\">vim</code> and press\nenter.  (Ensure you have no vim rc)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token function\">vim</span></code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>What are you thoughts?</li>\n<li>What are things you expected to see?</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/opening-vim","title":"Opening Vim","order":"4A","section":"Basics","description":"Lets open vim for the first time!"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"53A","path":"/pit-stop","title":"Pit Stop"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"54A","path":"/adv-motions","title":"Advanced Motions"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"50A","path":"/search-and-replace","title":"Search And Replace"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"51A","path":"/macros","title":"Macros"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"52A","path":"/registers","title":"Registers"}}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"order":"3A","path":"/are